\cb3 2. Why a Graph beats a Linear Pipeline\cb1 \
\cb3 In a simple linear chain (Binary \uc0\u8594  AES \u8594  Base64), data moves in one direction. In a Graph/FBP architecture, you can do things that are impossible with simple piping:\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Forking (Teeing): Send one data stream into two different codec chains simultaneously (e.g., save raw data to a log while sending encrypted data to a socket).\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Merging (Joining): Combine two streams (e.g., a data stream and a metadata stream) into a single codec that "wraps" them into a container format.\cb1 \
