\cb3 3. The "Endpoint" as a Type-Negotiator\cb1 \
\cb3 Your idea of "Endpoints" translating data types on the fly is a sophisticated solution to a classic FBP problem called "Interface Mismatch."\cb1 \
\
\cb3 In most FBP systems, if Node A sends a String and Node B expects a Uint8Array, the system crashes. By building "Translation Logic" into the Ports of your nodes:\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Implicit Conversion: The graph becomes "self-healing." If you drop an AES codec (Binary) after a Text generator, the Endpoint automatically spins up a TextEncoder to bridge the gap.\cb1 \
