\cb5 You've actually got two things in front of you: a long architectural conversation, and a critique of it. The critique is solid \'97 it correctly identifies the sycophancy, several real technical bugs (the `Buffer.from(data, 'base64')` direction error is genuine, the `Link.next` interface confusion is real), and the right next move (write the smallest working version). I agree with about 90% of it.\cb1 \
