\cb5 But there are a few places where even the critique is too generous to the original conversation, and several things both passes missed entirely. Here's what I'd add.\cb1 \
\
\cb5 ## Where the critique is right and worth doubling down on\cb1 \
\
\cb5 - 
\f2\b Async iterators as the primitive.
\f0\b0  This is the correct call. Every "I want pipelines with backpressure that work in Node and the browser" problem has converged on this since ~2019.\cb1 \
\cb5 - 
\f2\b "You don't need agents, you need typed dataflow nodes."
\f0\b0  Yes. The word "agentic" is doing a lot of unearned work in the original conversation.\cb1 \
